CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 3, 1959, pg. A2 reads: "Century Club Installation - New officers of the Century Club were installed Sept. 26 in meeting room of Fort Duquesne Post American Legion 755. Among those present were officers and members shown above.  Left to right, seated: Elbert Kennedy and Richard Dickson.  Standing, first row: Horton Johnson, Andrew Dixon, Andrew Wilson, John Johnson, Pronty L. Ford.  Second row: Wilber Miller, Isaac Magett, Robert Daniels, McKanic Goods.  Back row: T.V. Young, Carl Banks, Thomas Leach, Carl Morris and Paul Pollard.  Not present for the picture were Robert Wooden, John Harrell, Roland Myers, Archie Youngblood, George T. Cox and Roy Leach. - Harris Photo.""Century Club's New Officers Installed." Pittsburgh Courier (1955-1966), City Edition ed.: 1. Oct 03 1959. ProQuest. Web. 21 Mar. 2017 .
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Century Club officers and members, seated from left: Elbert Kennedy and Richard Dickson; standing, first row: Horton Johnson, Andrew Dixon, Andrew Wilson, John Johnson, Pronty L. Ford; second row: Wilber Miller, Isaac Magett, Robert Daniels, McKanic Goods; back row: T. V. Young, Carl Banks, Thomas Leach, Carl Morris, and Paul Pollard, gathered in Fort Duquesne Post American Legion 755
